snippet.textDisplay: I hate what suicide does to everyone it touches. For several years they blamed drugs and we had that useless stigma.  Then, when more and more well known names had not used drugs,  then it was bullying and each time we need more and more psychologists who add more and more drugs that in themselves cause suicide.  Now we have a world full of people taking psychotropic drugs.  For all he drugs and all the psychiatrists, the only thing that has really changed is people’s attitudes.  Its seen  as sad,  but nothing to do about it.  They know it;s an imbalance in the brain , just like a malignant cancer is a growth on the body.   One is acceptable to discuss, one is not.  Maybe it will be acceptable to ask for help one day without some stupid stigma.  We throw money at things, take every opportunity to create new drugs which cost more, have more side effects and work NO better, but we have to use them because they’re new and expensive.  But the  one thing people continue to  do especially well —is stigmatize.  Maybe one day we can overcome this and actually allow people to get the help they need, get the gov out of our Dr’s offices and end the stupid profitable war on drugs.
